options.description:
The city of Görlitz is located at the intersection of the railway lines Dresden-Wrocław and Berlin-Zittau (single-tracked).

The main station in Görlitz was opened in 1847. Until WW2, it was an important hub for inter-city travel troughout Germany, having 12 passenger tracks. Today, of the former 12 passenger tracks only 6 are left, and the station has since lost most of its importance, being only a regional transfer point.

This simulation is set in 2020. On the Dresden-Wrocław line, the simulation area extends from Gersdorf (which is the location of the first block signal after Görlitz) to the Germany-Poland border near Zgorzelec; on the Berlin-Zittau line from the passing track at Charlottenhof (which is not a passenger station) to Hagenwerder. It includes the Bahnbetriebswerk Görlitz, where the Länderbahn trains are maintained, as well as a simplified version of the sidings east of the station (Abstellanlage Ost). Further, there are access tracks to Versuchsanlage Schlauroth and the Waggonbau Görlitz wagon construction facility (currently owned by Bombardier Transportation).

Görlitz is served by two private railway companies: the Länderbahn GmbH operates services Dresden-Görlitz(-Wrocław), and the ODEG (Ostdeutsche Eisenbahn Gesellschaft) operates the services Cottbus-Zittau and Hoyerswerda-Görlitz.

The timetable of this simulation roughly orients on the real-world timetables of 2020. However, while in reality trains from/to Schlauroth or Waggonbauwerke are very scarce, this simulation includes multiple trains from/to these facilities in order to make operation more interesting.
options.title: Görlitz
